</section>

<section class="mission-details">
	<div class="mission-intro">
		
		<a name="eztoc22152650_1" id="eztoc22152650_1"></a><h2>The mission</h2><p>With global mean sea level rising because of climate change, Copernicus Sentinel-6 is the next radar altimetry reference mission to extend the legacy of sea-surface height measurements until at least 2030. The satellite carries a&nbsp;Poseidon-4 radar altimeter and a microwave radiometer.</p>
	</div>
	<div class="mission-data">
		
		<a name="eztoc22152651_1" id="eztoc22152651_1"></a><h2>The launch</h2><p>
<b>Date</b>: 21 November 2020<br />
<b>Site</b>: Vandenberg, California, US<br />
<b>Rocket</b>: SpaceX Falcon 9<br />&nbsp;</p>
	</div>
		<div class="mission-logo">
		<img src="/var/esa/storage/images/applications/observing_the_earth/copernicus/sentinel-6/22152652-41-eng-GB/Sentinel-6_pillars.jpg"> 
	</div>
	</section>

<section class="mission-stats connecting-benefiting">
	
		
		
<ul>

<li><a href="https://www.esa.int/Applications/Observing_the_Earth/Copernicus/Sentinel-6/A_rising_threat"><b>3.2 mm </b></a>yearly&nbsp;sea-level rise</li>

<li><a href="https://www.esa.int/Applications/Observing_the_Earth/Copernicus/Sentinel-6/Facts_and_figures"><b>1336 km</b></a>&nbsp;orbit altitude</li>

<li><a href="https://www.esa.int/Applications/Observing_the_Earth/Copernicus/Sentinel-6/Charting_sea_level"><b>66° </b></a>orbit&nbsp;inclination</li>

<li><a href="https://www.esa.int/Applications/Observing_the_Earth/Copernicus/Sentinel-6/Charting_sea_level"><b>95%</b></a>&nbsp;ocean measured</li>

</ul>

	
